messages.content: To install ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes, navigate to the ComfyUI/custom_nodes directory in your command line and run the following command: git clone https://github.com/an90ray/ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes.git
What should I do to update ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes?

To update ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes, navigate to the ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes directory and run the command: git pull https://github.com/an90ray/ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes.git
What are some other custom nodes that can be used with ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes?
Some other custom nodes that can be used with ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes include ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes, ComfyUI-Impact-Pack, and sdxl_prompt_styler.
What is the purpose of ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes?
ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes is a custom node for ComfyUI that allows for routing and organizing nodes in a workflow.
Are there any examples of using ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes with other custom nodes?
Yes, there are examples of using ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes with ComfyUI_Comfyroll_CustomNodes, ComfyUI-Impact-Pack, and sdxl_prompt_styler to create a styled grid workflow.
Where can I find a visual representation of a workflow using ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes?
A visual representation of a workflow using ComfyUI_RErouter_CustomNodes can be found in the 'workflows' directory, with the filename 'style_grid.jpg'.
Is there a preview image available for the styled grid workflow?
Yes, a preview image of the styled grid workflow is available in the 'workflows' directory, with the filename 'preview_workflow_style_grid.jpg'.
